Note that 
 \begin {align*}  D_{\mathrm {KL}}(P || Q) &= \mathbb {E}_P \left [\log \left (\frac {P(x)}{Q(x)}\right )\right ] \\ &= \mathbb {E}_P \left [-\log \left (\frac {Q(x)}{P(x)}\right )\right ] \\ \end {align*} 
By Jensen's Inequality,
   \begin {align*}     D_{\mathrm {KL}}(P || Q) &\geq  -\log  \left (\mathbb {E}_P \left [\frac {Q(x)}{P(x)}\right ]\right ) = 0   \end {align*}

Define p_i = \frac {a_i}{A}, q_i = \frac {b_i}{B}, then 
 \begin {align*}   D_{\mathrm {KL}}(p || q) &= \sum  \frac {a_i}{A} \log {\frac {B a_i}{A b_i}} \\   &= \sum  \frac {a_i}{A} \log {\frac {a_i}{b_i}} - \sum  \frac {a_i}{A} \log {\frac {A}{B}} \\   &= \sum  \frac {a_i}{A} \log {\frac {a_i}{b_i}} - \log {\frac {A}{B}} \\ \end {align*} 
By Gibb's inequality,
 \begin {align*}   \sum  \frac {a_i}{A} \log {\frac {a_i}{b_i}} - \log {\frac {A}{B}} \geq  0   &\implies    \sum  \frac {a_i}{A} \log {\frac {a_i}{b_i}} \geq  \log {\frac {A}{B}} \\   &\iff    A \sum  a_i \log {\frac {a_i}{b_i}} \geq  A \log {\frac {A}{B}} \end {align*} 
as desired.

