    Consider a smooth contained problem with \min _{\mathbf {x}}f(\mathbf {x}),\quad  \text {s.t.} \quad  r_{i}(\mathbf {x})\ =\ 0,\ 1\leq  i\leq  p, h_{j}(\mathbf {x})\ \leq \ 0,\ 1\leq  j\leq  q. Consider its Lagrangian function \mathscr {L}(\mathbf {x},\mathbf {u},\mathbf {v})\ =\ f(\mathbf {x})+\sum _{i=1}^{p}u_{i}\cdot  r_{i}(\mathbf {x})+\sum _{j=1}^{q}v_{j}\cdot  h_{j}(\mathbf {x}).
    KKT-conditions:

Stationary \nabla _{\mathbf {x}}{\mathcal {L}}(\mathbf {x_*},\mathbf {u_*},\mathbf {v_*})\;=\;\mathbf {0}

Primal Feasibility: \begin {array}{l}{{r_{i}(x_{\star })\ =\ 0,\ 1\leq  i\leq  p,}}\\ {{h_{j}(x_{\star })\ \leq \ 0,\ 1\leq  j\leq  q.}}\end {array}

Dual Feasibility: v_{\star }\geq  0.

Complimentary slackness: h_{j}(x_{\star })\cdot  v_{\star  j}\ =\ 0,\quad \forall \ 1\leq  j\leq  q.

Because \nabla  f is Lipschitz, by 1st-order Taylor approximation

f(\mathbf {x}^{\prime })\leq  f(\mathbf {x})+\langle \nabla  f(\mathbf {x}),\mathbf {x}^{\prime }-\mathbf {x}\rangle +\frac {L}{2}\left ||\mathbf {x}^{\prime }-\mathbf {x}\right ||_{2}^{2},\quad \forall \ \mathbf {x}^{\prime },\mathbf {x}
Now take \mathbf {x}' = \mathbf {x} - \tau  \nabla  f( \mathbf {x}). Then
   \begin {align*}     f(\mathbf {x}^{\prime }) &\leq  f(\mathbf {x})+ \tau  ||\nabla  f( \mathbf {x} )||_2^2 + \frac {\tau ^2 L}{2} ||\nabla  f( \mathbf {x})||_2^2 \\     &= f( \mathbf {x}) - \tau (1 - \frac {\tau  L}{2})||\nabla  f( \mathbf {x})||_2^2   \end {align*} 
  Take \tau  = \frac {1}{L}, such that
     \begin {align*} f( \mathbf {x}) - \tau (1 - \frac {\tau  L}{2})||\nabla  f( \mathbf {x})||_2^2 &= f( \mathbf {x}) - \frac {1}{2L}||\nabla  f( \mathbf {x})||_2^2     \end {align*}

Given f is convex and smooth, and \mathbf {x}_* is an optimal solution, then
f(\mathbf {x}_{\star })\geq  f(\mathbf {x})+\nabla  f(\mathbf {x})^{\top }(\mathbf {x}_{\star }-\mathbf {x})
Flipping the inequality yields
f(\mathbf {x})\leq  f(\mathbf {x}_{\star })+\nabla  f(\mathbf {x})^{\top }(\mathbf {x}-\mathbf {x}_{\star })
By previous lemma, taking \mathbf {x}' = \mathbf {x} - \frac {1}{L} \nabla  f( \mathbf {x}) yields
f(\mathbf {x}^{\prime })\leq  f(\mathbf {x})-{\frac {1}{2L}}\left ||\nabla  f(\mathbf {x})\right ||_{2}^{2}
such that
f(\mathbf {x}^{\prime })\leq  f(\mathbf {x}_{\star })+\nabla  f(\mathbf {x})^{\top }(\mathbf {x}-\mathbf {x}_{\star })-{\frac {1}{2L}}\left ||\nabla  f(\mathbf {x})\right ||_{2}^{2}
Equivalently,
f(\mathbf {x}^{\prime })-f(\mathbf {x}_{\star })\leq {\frac {L}{2}}\left [{\frac {2}{L}}\nabla  f(\mathbf {x})^{\top }(\mathbf {x}-\mathbf {x}_{\star })-{\frac {1}{L^{2}}}\left ||\nabla  f(\mathbf {x})\right ||_{2}^{2}\right ]
Completing the square,
 \begin {align*}  f(\mathbf {x}^{\prime })-f(\mathbf {x}_{\star })&\leq \frac {L}{2}\left [\frac {2}{L}\nabla  f(\mathbf {x})^{\top }(\mathbf {x}-\mathbf {x}_{\star })-\frac {1}{L^{2}}\left ||\nabla  f(\mathbf {x})\right ||_{2}^{2}\right ] \\   &=\frac {L}{2}\left [\left ||\mathbf {x}-\mathbf {x}_{\star }\right ||_{2}^{2}-\left ||\mathbf {x}-\frac {1}{L}\nabla  f(\mathbf {x})-\mathbf {x}_{\star }\right ||_{2}^{2}\right ] \\   &=\frac {L}{2}\left [\left ||\mathbf {x}-\mathbf {x}_{\star }\right ||_{2}^{2}-\left ||\mathbf {x}^{\prime }-\mathbf {x}_{\star }\right ||_{2}^{2}\right ] \end {align*} 
Let \mathbf {x}_{k}=\mathbf {x}_{k-1}-\frac {1}{L}\nabla  f(\mathbf {x}_{k-1}), then we have

 \begin {align*}  \sum _{i=1}^{k}\left (f(\mathbf {x}_{i})-f(\mathbf {x}_{\star })\right ) &\leq  \frac {L}{2}\sum _{i=1}^{k}\left [\left ||\mathbf {x}_{i-1}-\mathbf {x}_{\star }\right ||_{2}^{2}-\left ||\mathbf {x}_{i}-\mathbf {x}_{\star }\right ||_{2}^{2}\right ]  \\ &=\frac {L}{2}\left [\left ||\mathbf {x}_{0}-\mathbf {x}_{\star }\right ||_{2}^{2}-\left ||\mathbf {x}_{k}-\mathbf {x}_{0}\right ||_{2}^{2}\right ] \\   &\leq \frac {L}{2}\left ||\mathbf {x}_{0}-\mathbf {x}_{\star }\right ||_{2}^{2}  \end {align*} 
Therefore, given f(\mathbf {x}_{k})-f(\mathbf {x}_{\star })\leq  f(\mathbf {x}_{i})-f(\mathbf {x}_{*}) \text { for } \forall  i\leq  k\,,

k\left (f(\mathbf {x}_{k})-f(\mathbf {x}_{\star })\right )\leq \sum _{i=1}^{k}\left (f(\mathbf {x}_{i})-f(\mathbf {x}_{\star })\right )\leq \frac {L}{2}\left ||\mathbf {x}_{0}-\mathbf {x}_{\star }\right ||_{2}^{2}

